						<summary>

						<p>Pillar built into the threshold of the entrance into the compound of the Vēnugōpālasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>13th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription can be assigned to the 13th century A.D. on the basis of palaeography and internal evidences.</p>						

						<p>Much damaged and worn out. Describes a chief belonging to Ḻonkula family and attributed with a string of epithets such as <hi rend="italic">Sōmakula kamalendu</hi> holding <hi rend="italic">Kapidhvaja.</hi> It registers a gift of land, cow <hi rend="italic">(mōdālu)</hi> for maintaining a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mallikārjuna. The gift is stated to have been entrusted to certain Appanabōya for its maintenance.</p>						

						</summary>
